1. Design Schema:
Company (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  created_at TIMESTAMP
) // One company → many warehouses, products, suppliers

Warehouse (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  company_id UUID REFERENCES Company(id),
  name VARCHAR(255),
  location VARCHAR(255),
  created_at TIMESTAMP
)

Product (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  company_id UUID REFERENCES Company(id),
  name VARCHAR(255),
  sku VARCHAR(100) UNIQUE,
  price DECIMAL(10,2),
  is_bundle BOOLEAN DEFAULT FALSE,
  created_at TIMESTAMP
)

Inventory (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  product_id UUID REFERENCES Product(id),
  warehouse_id UUID REFERENCES Warehouse(id),
  quantity INT NOT NULL,
  updated_at TIMESTAMP,
  UNIQUE(product_id, warehouse_id)
)

Supplier (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  company_id UUID REFERENCES Company(id),
  name VARCHAR(255),
  contact_info TEXT
)

SupplierProduct (
  supplier_id UUID REFERENCES Supplier(id),
  product_id UUID REFERENCES Product(id),
  PRIMARY KEY (supplier_id, product_id)
) // One supplier → many products, One product → many suppliers

2. Identified Gaps (Questions for Product Team)
  1. Are SKUs global or company-specific?
  2. Are warehouse-to-warehouse transfers allowed?
  3. Is bundle price calculated or fixed?
  4. Do suppliers have product-specific pricing?
  5. Is multi-currency pricing needed?
  6. Should inventory changes be reversible?

3. Indexes & Constraints
    UNIQUE (sku)
    UNIQUE (product_id, warehouse_id)
    INDEX (company_id)
    INDEX (product_id)
    INDEX (warehouse_id)
